255
00:17:03.690 --> 00:17:04.690
Mom…

256
00:17:05.980 --> 00:17:07.650
I thought it was real.

257
00:17:08.940 --> 00:17:10.376
I did.

258
00:17:10.400 --> 00:17:13.626
And I gave him every last bit of me.

259
00:17:13.650 --> 00:17:15.586
But I don't want to do that again.

260
00:17:15.610 --> 00:17:18.756
I never want to feel that
way again. with anyone.

261
00:17:18.780 --> 00:17:19.950
Don't do that.

262
00:17:20.540 --> 00:17:22.290
Don't shut down.

263
00:17:23.960 --> 00:17:28.540
When your father died.
I let that be all there is.

264
00:17:30.710 --> 00:17:32.630
Be better than me.

265
00:17:34.340 --> 00:17:35.510
Robert wasn't the one.

266
00:17:36.550 --> 00:17:38.390
The end.

267
00:17:39.760 --> 00:17:41.350
But your friends…

268
00:17:41.930 --> 00:17:43.326
Eleanor.

269
00:17:43.350 --> 00:17:49.060
you have found people
to love. share your life with.

270
00:17:49.860 --> 00:17:52.546
Obviously I did not teach you that.

271
00:17:52.570 --> 00:17:55.530
but you figured it out on your own.

272
00:17:56.740 --> 00:17:57.740
And these people.

273
00:17:58.740 --> 00:18:00.990
if you really love them.

274
00:18:02.330 --> 00:18:04.580
then you have got to show them.

275
00:18:06.540 --> 00:18:08.306
And that means you've
got to go back there.

276
00:18:08.330 --> 00:18:11.670
Go back there and
see this thing through.

277
00:18:12.710 --> 00:18:15.300
Because if you don't. trust me.

278
00:18:16.470 --> 00:18:18.220
you'll become what you deride.

279
00:18:19.720 --> 00:18:23.270
A hardened woman who
can barely get through lunch

280
00:18:24.980 --> 00:18:27.350
with the person she loves the most.

281
00:18:37.280 --> 00:18:38.796
What do you want me to do?

282
00:18:38.820 --> 00:18:40.370
I mean. yeah. baby.

283
00:18:43.490 --> 00:18:45.250
Okay. Well. then you call him.

284
00:19:02.930 --> 00:19:04.600
- Hello.
- Please.

285
00:19:07.180 --> 00:19:08.810
He'll be here any minute.

286
00:19:30.750 --> 00:19:31.830
I didn't kill her.

287
00:19:34.500 --> 00:19:35.710
And I told the cops that.

288
00:19:36.800 --> 00:19:38.276
They don't believe me.

289
00:19:38.300 --> 00:19:40.696
They're making it out
like I went after her.

290
00:19:40.720 --> 00:19:44.100
But she called me a couple
of nights before she died.

291
00:19:50.810 --> 00:19:53.480
Well. if it isn't fancy Nancy in the flesh.

292
00:19:56.570 --> 00:19:58.320
You still wear the same Cologne.

293
00:20:00.490 --> 00:20:01.490
Beer.

294
00:20:06.830 --> 00:20:07.950
Real nice ring.

295
00:20:16.920 --> 00:20:17.920
So. what?

296
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:21.380
We're gonna have a staring contest?

297
00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:29.810
I was a child.

298
00:20:32.810 --> 00:20:35.650
The things you did to
me… I was just a child.

299
00:20:36.860 --> 00:20:37.916
A waste of time.

300
00:20:37.940 --> 00:20:40.626
No. you're gonna sit the
fuck down and listen to me.

301
00:20:40.650 --> 00:20:41.650
Easy. all right?

302
00:20:46.740 --> 00:20:48.370
Yeah. she told me everything.

303
00:20:48.870 --> 00:20:50.676
She was fucking your husband.

304
00:20:50.700 --> 00:20:52.370
Lying to everyone about it.

305
00:20:53.540 --> 00:20:54.960
Said he was a real creep too.

306
00:20:55.630 --> 00:20:57.170
Wouldn't take no for an answer.

307
00:20:58.710 --> 00:21:01.196
He even sent her naked pictures.

308
00:21:01.220 --> 00:21:02.420
Her husband saw 'em.

309
00:21:03.470 --> 00:21:05.590
It seemed like she didn't
have nobody to talk to.

310
00:21:06.470 --> 00:21:07.550
So that's what we did.

311
00:21:09.770 --> 00:21:13.270
A couple of days later she
called again. and she's at some…

312
00:21:14.390 --> 00:21:17.246
Some birthday thing… no. No. I'm sorry.

313
00:21:17.270 --> 00:21:19.376
This… none of this makes any sense.

314
00:21:19.400 --> 00:21:21.820
She never would have
called you. She hated you.

315
00:21:22.570 --> 00:21:24.126
You ruined her life.

316
00:21:24.150 --> 00:21:26.216
She wanted my protection.

317
00:21:26.240 --> 00:21:27.296
How?

318
00:21:27.320 --> 00:21:29.216
How were you going to protect her?

319
00:21:29.240 --> 00:21:30.540
She wanted me to scare him.

320
00:21:31.910 --> 00:21:33.556
Rough him up a bit.

321
00:21:33.580 --> 00:21:35.170
Get him to back off.

322
00:21:35.670 --> 00:21:37.356
I was going to do it too.

323
00:21:37.380 --> 00:21:38.670
I owed her that much.

324
00:22:07.110 --> 00:22:09.780
- Get back here.
- Sto… hey.

325
00:22:10.410 --> 00:22:12.466
- This has to stop.
- Hello?

326
00:22:12.490 --> 00:22:13.830
I have to tell her.

327
00:22:14.790 --> 00:22:16.396
- You don't mean that.
- Where are you?

328
00:22:16.420 --> 00:22:18.476
She may never speak to
me again. but she deserves

329
00:22:18.500 --> 00:22:20.060
- to know the truth.
- Can you hear me?

330
00:22:23.510 --> 00:22:24.630
Shit.

331
00:22:45.360 --> 00:22:47.860
He was… he was leaned over her…

332
00:22:48.490 --> 00:22:49.490
Her body.

333
00:22:50.870 --> 00:22:54.080
Doing something with her…
her hand. I didn't see what.

334
00:22:56.710 --> 00:22:58.750
You just left her there?

335
00:22:59.460 --> 00:23:01.356
What was I supposed to do?

336
00:23:01.380 --> 00:23:02.540
You call for help.

337
00:23:04.050 --> 00:23:05.276
You tell the police.

338
00:23:05.300 --> 00:23:07.300
You're going to tell me
what I should have done?

339
00:23:08.130 --> 00:23:10.486
Your husband killed your best friend.

340
00:23:10.510 --> 00:23:12.576
What the fuck are you
going to do about it?

341
00:23:12.600 --> 00:23:15.520
'Cause I tried telling them
and no one would believe me.

342
00:23:19.650 --> 00:23:20.650
Where are you going?

343
00:23:21.270 --> 00:23:22.360
To the police station.

344
00:23:23.020 --> 00:23:24.150
I'm coming with you.

345
00:23:49.340 --> 00:23:51.566
They said they had urgent
information about the hennessey case.

346
00:23:51.590 --> 00:23:53.866
- Thought you'd want to hear it.
- I have a press conference to get to.

347
00:23:53.890 --> 00:23:55.406
- Make it quick.
- We went to see Scott.

348
00:23:55.430 --> 00:23:57.826
- I am aware.
- Detective. he's telling the truth.

349
00:23:57.850 --> 00:23:59.286
And your evidence is?

350
00:23:59.310 --> 00:24:01.286
Him. Him. He is an eyewitness.

351
00:24:01.310 --> 00:24:02.416
He saw Howard do it.

352
00:24:02.440 --> 00:24:04.336
He has details about
the crime because...

353
00:24:04.360 --> 00:24:06.296
- yes. because he committed it.
- No.

354
00:24:06.320 --> 00:24:08.360
Why does it feel like
you want it to be him?

355
00:24:09.150 --> 00:24:11.296
Let me tell you how this works.

356
00:24:11.320 --> 00:24:15.346
In here. I have physical.
verifiable. concrete evidence.

357
00:24:15.370 --> 00:24:16.926
- Yes. but you s...
- I have phone records.

358
00:24:16.950 --> 00:24:18.136
prints on the victim's phone.

359
00:24:18.160 --> 00:24:21.766
I even have a series of threatening
Instagram messages from Mr. Reed.

360
00:24:21.790 --> 00:24:23.766
- Just talk to him. Just…
- that gives me motive.

361
00:24:23.790 --> 00:24:27.396
I have everything I need to
present this to the da's office.

362
00:24:27.420 --> 00:24:30.896
And I have a sea of reporters
waiting to hear the good news

363
00:24:30.920 --> 00:24:33.276
that the victim of a heinous
crime is going to get justice.

364
00:24:33.300 --> 00:24:37.736
So. unless you have something better
than what I have. we are done here.

365
00:24:37.760 --> 00:24:40.270
- His…
- what about Howard's phone or his laptop?

366
00:24:41.270 --> 00:24:43.166
Everything we've given
you so far is circumstantial.

367
00:24:43.190 --> 00:24:46.036
But what if we had something
that connected Howard to Nancy?

368
00:24:46.060 --> 00:24:49.416
Someone texted nudes
of Nancy to her phone.

369
00:24:49.440 --> 00:24:51.126
Howard has to have those pictures.

370
00:24:51.150 --> 00:24:53.360
Can you get a warrant
to search his computer?

371
00:24:54.280 --> 00:24:55.346
We're done here.

372
00:24:55.370 --> 00:24:57.466
What? Detective. are
you fucking serious?

373
00:24:57.490 --> 00:24:59.516
- Okay. Hey. Mary! Mary.
- You have to do your job!

374
00:24:59.540 --> 00:25:00.846
- Stop. I know.
- This is her job.

375
00:25:00.870 --> 00:25:03.230
- But clearly she doesn't give a shit.
- Stop it. Not here.

376
00:25:03.870 --> 00:25:04.920
Let's go.

377
00:25:05.830 --> 00:25:06.840
Please.

378
00:25:09.210 --> 00:25:10.686
I have to go to court tomorrow.

379
00:25:10.710 --> 00:25:12.646
And I have nothing.

380
00:25:12.670 --> 00:25:15.866
Howard is going to take my girls.
He's going to take my fucking kids. Ellie.

381
00:25:15.890 --> 00:25:18.076
- Are you high?
- What? No!

382
00:25:18.100 --> 00:25:20.310
You told me you weren't
taking those pills anymore.

383
00:25:20.970 --> 00:25:22.996
I didn't start until after Nancy died. okay?

384
00:25:23.020 --> 00:25:25.520
- So you lied.
- I didn't think you would understand.

385
00:25:26.770 --> 00:25:29.376
You had so much going on.

386
00:25:29.400 --> 00:25:34.086
And you were able to handle
it so much better. And I just…

387
00:25:34.110 --> 00:25:35.860
I felt like I was underwater.

388
00:25:36.450 --> 00:25:41.886
And everything took so much effort
and I couldn't focus with the kids.

389
00:25:41.910 --> 00:25:44.896
I just… I needed something
just to get me going.

390
00:25:44.920 --> 00:25:49.106
You sat on this couch and you
told me everything about Howard.

391
00:25:49.130 --> 00:25:51.316
and the cheating. everything that he did.

392
00:25:51.340 --> 00:25:54.196
But you were still keeping shit from me.

393
00:25:54.220 --> 00:25:57.566
Mary. how are we looking each
other in the eye and just lying?

394
00:25:57.590 --> 00:25:58.906
I don't know! You tell me.

395
00:25:58.930 --> 00:26:01.866
I don't know. It's not just
me. It's you. it's me. it's Nancy.

396
00:26:01.890 --> 00:26:03.956
Nancy was lying.

397
00:26:03.980 --> 00:26:07.480
She was talking to
Scott and we had no idea!

398
00:26:08.060 --> 00:26:12.570
I know. I know. I know. I know.

399
00:26:16.110 --> 00:26:20.580
Mary. that night after we
all left your birthday dinner.

400
00:26:21.580 --> 00:26:24.200
I was standing at the valet. waiting.

401
00:26:25.210 --> 00:26:26.710
And Nancy came back.

402
00:26:28.420 --> 00:26:32.500
And she asked me to
go with her. and I said no.

403
00:26:33.550 --> 00:26:39.446
She was trying to be honest
with me and I wouldn't let her.

404
00:26:39.470 --> 00:26:44.826
And now she's gone and I have
been so scared to say that out loud.

405
00:26:44.850 --> 00:26:47.560
But I don't… I don't want
to hold on to it anymore.

406
00:26:58.110 --> 00:27:01.490
I wasn't just stealing Nancy's things.

407
00:27:03.370 --> 00:27:05.290
Howard and I would sometimes…

408
00:27:07.580 --> 00:27:09.396
Every once in a while when we had sex.

409
00:27:09.420 --> 00:27:12.540
we would role-play and we
would pretend we were them.

410
00:27:13.300 --> 00:27:15.260
I used to pretend I was her.

411
00:27:16.880 --> 00:27:19.510
Friends don't do that. Do they?

412
00:27:22.140 --> 00:27:26.286
And sometimes I think.
maybe I was contributing to this.

413
00:27:26.310 --> 00:27:27.940
To Howard wanting her.

414
00:27:30.810 --> 00:27:32.786
I'm sorry. but I thought if you knew that.

415
00:27:32.810 --> 00:27:35.570
there was no way you
would ever love me anymore.

416
00:27:37.820 --> 00:27:40.950
I think we were all
scared of the same thing.

417
00:27:50.580 --> 00:27:54.146
Every day at three o'clock I
peel and cut this apple for Artie.

418
00:27:54.170 --> 00:27:56.420
And I leave a whole one for junie.

419
00:27:57.090 --> 00:27:58.316
Every day.

420
00:27:58.340 --> 00:28:01.890
It's one of a million things that I do

421
00:28:02.590 --> 00:28:08.520
to keep their lives predictable
and to make them feel safe.

422
00:28:12.270 --> 00:28:13.650
Howard doesn't know about it.

423
00:28:18.650 --> 00:28:20.610
No one does 'cause it's invisible.

424
00:28:27.740 --> 00:28:29.710
It's my kids who are gonna suffer.

425
00:28:39.090 --> 00:28:40.670
What do we do now?

426
00:28:41.800 --> 00:28:43.470
We start with the truth.

427
00:28:51.310 --> 00:28:52.900
I'm gonna talk to Cora.

428
00:28:54.060 --> 00:28:56.876
I thought that as her
father you should know.

429
00:28:56.900 --> 00:29:00.086
that I'm… I'm gonna tell her everything.

430
00:29:00.110 --> 00:29:02.296
About us. about Nancy and Scott.

431
00:29:02.320 --> 00:29:04.660
I think if Nancy had more time.

432
00:29:05.320 --> 00:29:08.136
she would have been honest
with Cora about her past.

433
00:29:08.160 --> 00:29:09.886
No. Absolutely not.

434
00:29:09.910 --> 00:29:13.596
Robert. you may be
fine with all these secrets

435
00:29:13.620 --> 00:29:17.250
because you're a hennessey. but I'm not.

436
00:29:18.130 --> 00:29:20.776
I can't. I don't want to live like this.

437
00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:23.510
These secrets killed Nancy.

438
00:29:24.680 --> 00:29:26.826
I don't want that for Cora.

439
00:29:26.850 --> 00:29:30.406
I hurt her and I owe her the truth.

440
00:29:30.430 --> 00:29:32.286
The truth? She already
thinks I'm an asshole.

441
00:29:32.310 --> 00:29:33.910
And you're just gonna
make things worse.

442
00:29:34.690 --> 00:29:36.440
This isn't about you.

443
00:29:37.110 --> 00:29:38.706
- It isn't?
- No.

444
00:29:38.730 --> 00:29:41.280
This isn't about me not
giving you what you want?

445
00:29:42.820 --> 00:29:44.360
What you've always wanted?

446
00:29:46.660 --> 00:29:47.660
No.

447
00:29:49.490 --> 00:29:50.490
No.

448
00:29:51.620 --> 00:29:54.540
I used to want something from you.

449
00:29:56.120 --> 00:29:57.960
But I don't anymore.

450
00:30:00.170 --> 00:30:02.130
I'm gonna talk to Cora.

451
00:30:03.470 --> 00:30:05.470
You should take care of yourself.

452
00:30:05.970 --> 00:30:07.430
- Eleanor.
- Yes?

453
00:30:10.720 --> 00:30:12.140
I'm really sorry.

454
00:30:30.200 --> 00:30:31.596
I still wanna be there.

455
00:30:31.620 --> 00:30:32.676
I know.

456
00:30:32.700 --> 00:30:36.750
The best thing you can do for me
right now is to watch your sisters. okay?

457
00:30:37.370 --> 00:30:38.790
You think he'll win?

458
00:30:39.960 --> 00:30:41.840
Your aunt Ellie and I have a plan.

459
00:30:43.300 --> 00:30:44.590
I love you. sweetheart.

460
00:30:45.130 --> 00:30:46.680
Give the girls a hug for me.

461
00:30:48.180 --> 00:30:49.220
I will.

462
00:30:50.010 --> 00:30:51.970
- I love you too.
- Bye.

463
00:30:56.520 --> 00:30:59.036
I had never met anyone like Mary.

464
00:30:59.060 --> 00:31:00.206
None of us had.

465
00:31:00.230 --> 00:31:04.190
She's like empathy personified.

466
00:31:04.860 --> 00:31:10.216
She always has space in that huge.
expansive heart of hers for everyone.

467
00:31:10.240 --> 00:31:13.016
But especially for her children.

468
00:31:13.040 --> 00:31:17.960
No one means more to Mary than
Marcus and Juniper. and Artemis.

469
00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:20.380
Thank you. Ms. Bouchet.

470
00:31:23.500 --> 00:31:24.760
Ms. Bouchet.

471
00:31:26.220 --> 00:31:29.406
do you recall an incident
involving the respondent

472
00:31:29.430 --> 00:31:33.180
and her then eight-year-old daughter
during the month of October 2025?

473
00:31:33.890 --> 00:31:35.406
I would have to check my calendar.

474
00:31:35.430 --> 00:31:37.076
That's okay. I'll be specific.

475
00:31:37.100 --> 00:31:42.246
On October 19th. 2025. were
you aware that Mrs. Simpson.

476
00:31:42.270 --> 00:31:46.126
under the influence of
illegally procured amphetamines

477
00:31:46.150 --> 00:31:48.086
drove away from an arco gas station

478
00:31:48.110 --> 00:31:50.860
while her daughter. Juniper.
was still inside the mini-mart?

479
00:31:57.160 --> 00:31:58.500
Yes.

480
00:31:59.250 --> 00:32:00.920
Yes. What?

481
00:32:02.250 --> 00:32:04.936
Yes. I am aware that happened.

482
00:32:04.960 --> 00:32:06.486
She's human. She made a mistake.

483
00:32:06.510 --> 00:32:08.396
And on the morning of June fourth.

484
00:32:08.420 --> 00:32:11.276
were you with her when her
youngest daughter was admitted

485
00:32:11.300 --> 00:32:13.826
- to the emergency room having overdosed…
- I told you that wasn't me.

486
00:32:13.850 --> 00:32:15.286
- That was Howard.
- …On Mrs. Simpson's

487
00:32:15.310 --> 00:32:17.180
unprescribed Adderall?

488
00:32:21.480 --> 00:32:23.246
Yes. I was at the hospital.

489
00:32:23.270 --> 00:32:24.440
Thank you.

490
00:32:25.270 --> 00:32:26.780
No further questions. your honor.

491
00:32:27.690 --> 00:32:29.070
You can step down.

492
00:32:31.280 --> 00:32:33.280
Any further witnesses. Ms. Tisdall?

493
00:32:35.410 --> 00:32:36.926
Actually yes. your honor.

494
00:32:36.950 --> 00:32:38.580
She's just arrived.

495
00:32:49.210 --> 00:32:52.300
I was married to Howard for eight years.

496
00:32:53.010 --> 00:32:54.340
Did you have any children?

497
00:32:56.100 --> 00:33:00.680
None. to Howard's
profound disappointment.

498
00:33:02.350 --> 00:33:05.310
I did get pregnant. but then I lost it.

499
00:33:05.940 --> 00:33:10.820
Looking back. it was the
biggest blessing of my life.

500
00:33:11.450 --> 00:33:13.700
Why? If you don't mind.

501
00:33:15.660 --> 00:33:17.950
Because humanity would be better off

502
00:33:18.490 --> 00:33:20.700
if some people didn't procreate.

503
00:33:22.120 --> 00:33:25.186
It sounds like you didn't
care much for your husband.

504
00:33:25.210 --> 00:33:27.106
I did at first.

505
00:33:27.130 --> 00:33:32.550
Howard has this way of
charming you through repulsion.

506
00:33:33.760 --> 00:33:36.800
It took eight years at least
before he lay his hands on me.

507
00:33:38.140 --> 00:33:39.430
It was only once. but…

508
00:33:41.350 --> 00:33:42.480
It was memorable.

509
00:33:45.190 --> 00:33:48.166
I spent the last two decades terrified

510
00:33:48.190 --> 00:33:51.860
that he would find me
and finish what he started.

511
00:33:53.150 --> 00:33:55.426
But I just look at him now

512
00:33:55.450 --> 00:33:58.660
and all I see is this angry child

513
00:33:59.280 --> 00:34:03.660
scared to death of his own mediocrity.

514
00:34:16.840 --> 00:34:18.220
All rise.

515
00:34:22.770 --> 00:34:23.770
Please sit.

516
00:34:26.520 --> 00:34:27.666
All right.

517
00:34:27.690 --> 00:34:30.876
When it comes to the emergency
order to request permission

518
00:34:30.900 --> 00:34:35.360
to relocate the children across
state lines. that request is denied.

519
00:34:36.900 --> 00:34:38.596
What does that mean? My job is in Ohio.

520
00:34:38.620 --> 00:34:40.006
That means get a new job.

521
00:34:40.030 --> 00:34:42.806
And given the pending
endangerment charges

522
00:34:42.830 --> 00:34:44.790
the respondent is currently facing.

523
00:34:45.580 --> 00:34:47.580
I am of the opinion
that the minor children.

524
00:34:48.330 --> 00:34:51.816
Artemis and Juniper Simpson.
are indeed in imminent harm

525
00:34:51.840 --> 00:34:54.896
and not safe to reside with
either parent at this time.

526
00:34:54.920 --> 00:34:56.316
- What?
- I am referring the matter

527
00:34:56.340 --> 00:34:59.066
to the department of
children and family services

528
00:34:59.090 --> 00:35:00.576
- to request…
- no.

529
00:35:00.600 --> 00:35:02.786
…temporary detention of the children.

530
00:35:02.810 --> 00:35:04.286
Once the case is resolved.

531
00:35:04.310 --> 00:35:08.166
we will reconvene and
assess our options long-term.

532
00:35:08.190 --> 00:35:09.400
Court is dismissed.

533
00:35:10.690 --> 00:35:11.796
We have options.

534
00:35:11.820 --> 00:35:12.956
It's gonna be okay.

535
00:35:12.980 --> 00:35:14.070
What happens now?

536
00:35:16.860 --> 00:35:19.086
- This wasn't supposed to happen this way.
- I know. I know.

537
00:35:19.110 --> 00:35:20.620
This wasn't supposed to happen.

538
00:35:21.830 --> 00:35:23.266
We will fight this.

539
00:35:23.290 --> 00:35:25.386
- What is wrong with you?
- No. No. no. no. no.

540
00:35:25.410 --> 00:35:27.436
- What the fuck is wrong with you?
- Stop it.

541
00:35:27.460 --> 00:35:31.460
I will come to the hotel and get
you. and you will stay with me.

542
00:35:47.520 --> 00:35:48.560
Ellie?

543
00:36:17.300 --> 00:36:18.420
Mare?

544
00:36:23.720 --> 00:36:25.140
Mary?

545
00:36:39.240 --> 00:36:41.466
Hey. you've reached Mary and junie.

546
00:36:41.490 --> 00:36:42.886
And me!

547
00:36:42.910 --> 00:36:43.990
Come on.

548
00:36:48.950 --> 00:36:50.266
Aunt Ellie?

549
00:36:50.290 --> 00:36:52.436
Hey. have you heard from your mom?

550
00:36:52.460 --> 00:36:53.516
My mom? No.

551
00:36:53.540 --> 00:36:54.936
Is your father there?

552
00:36:54.960 --> 00:36:56.710
No. no. I haven't seen him.

553
00:36:57.380 --> 00:36:58.986
I was watching junie and Artie

554
00:36:59.010 --> 00:37:01.606
and the social services
people came and took them.

555
00:37:01.630 --> 00:37:03.616
I'm not sure what to do.

556
00:37:03.640 --> 00:37:07.236
Okay. I'm gonna text you the
number for detective Bethany ganz.

557
00:37:07.260 --> 00:37:08.366
I want you to call her.

558
00:37:08.390 --> 00:37:11.206
There's something that I need
you to get to her from me. Okay?

559
00:37:11.230 --> 00:37:13.270
Yeah. Yeah. yeah. yeah. okay.

560
00:37:18.650 --> 00:37:19.650
You're gonna kill me?

561
00:37:21.650 --> 00:37:22.950
No. you're gonna kill you.

562
00:37:23.910 --> 00:37:25.030
Writes itself. really.

563
00:37:25.620 --> 00:37:27.386
Drug-addicted mother loses her kids.

564
00:37:27.410 --> 00:37:29.240
She's been in free fall for months.

565
00:37:29.830 --> 00:37:32.686
Nothing to live for. So she
slits her wrists and bleeds out

566
00:37:32.710 --> 00:37:35.210
in the very same spot where
her best friend was murdered.

567
00:37:38.340 --> 00:37:40.210
Eleanor and I spoke to Scott.

568
00:37:44.130 --> 00:37:45.140
He saw you.

569
00:37:46.430 --> 00:37:49.010
He saw you do it. He saw you kill Nancy.

570
00:37:50.060 --> 00:37:53.270
She asked him to meet her here.

571
00:37:54.020 --> 00:37:59.980
And she asked him to hurt you.
so that you would leave her alone.

572
00:38:01.070 --> 00:38:02.150
You're lying.

573
00:38:03.150 --> 00:38:05.990
Am I? Am I lying?

574
00:38:06.700 --> 00:38:09.740
You said that you knew
Nancy better than I did.

575
00:38:10.740 --> 00:38:12.516
Is that something that
she'd be capable of?

576
00:38:12.540 --> 00:38:14.620
Why am I free while he's in jail?

577
00:38:15.250 --> 00:38:16.250
Because…

578
00:38:17.500 --> 00:38:21.920
Because detective ganz
needs solid proof that you did it.

579
00:38:22.510 --> 00:38:24.170
And Ellie and I are supposed to get it.

580
00:38:25.090 --> 00:38:28.890
We are… we're supposed to
meet her in my hotel room tonight.

581
00:38:30.350 --> 00:38:31.680
And now I won't be there.

582
00:38:34.810 --> 00:38:39.060
Detective ganz will never
think that I killed myself.

583
00:38:41.110 --> 00:38:43.610
She will know that you did it.

584
00:38:45.240 --> 00:38:46.506
Listen to me. Howard.

585
00:38:46.530 --> 00:38:47.796
Listen to me.

586
00:38:47.820 --> 00:38:49.870
There's only one thing
for you to do here. okay?

587
00:38:50.450 --> 00:38:52.216
You let me call Ellie.

588
00:38:52.240 --> 00:38:56.040
Listen to me. I will tell her that it's off.

589
00:38:56.540 --> 00:38:57.880
I can't do it.

590
00:39:00.250 --> 00:39:01.550
And you run.

591
00:39:03.760 --> 00:39:05.970
You go.

592
00:39:07.180 --> 00:39:09.180
You do not take the girls.

593
00:39:09.760 --> 00:39:11.260
You don't want the girls.

594
00:39:14.520 --> 00:39:16.940
Just go.

595
00:39:19.810 --> 00:39:23.110
And you will finally be free.

596
00:39:27.490 --> 00:39:28.740
Let me call her.

597
00:39:29.740 --> 00:39:30.780
Okay?

598
00:39:32.580 --> 00:39:33.700
It's okay.

599
00:39:39.080 --> 00:39:40.540
Shit! Damn it!

600
00:39:48.260 --> 00:39:50.316
Damn it! Fuck. Howard!

601
00:39:50.340 --> 00:39:51.576
You brought me to a dead zone.

602
00:39:51.600 --> 00:39:53.366
It's not even gonna go through.

603
00:39:53.390 --> 00:39:54.446
Enough of this.

604
00:39:54.470 --> 00:39:56.810
We stick to the plan.
Get up. Come on. Move.

605
00:39:58.690 --> 00:40:00.940
The dead zone. The
victim was murdered here.

606
00:40:02.060 --> 00:40:03.796
My god. Dead zone.

607
00:40:03.820 --> 00:40:05.150
Shit!

608
00:40:08.650 --> 00:40:09.780
Walk.

609
00:40:11.910 --> 00:40:14.806
- When did you stop loving me?
- Come on. Come on.

610
00:40:14.830 --> 00:40:15.830
No!

611
00:40:17.200 --> 00:40:20.056
I gave you my whole adult life.

612
00:40:20.080 --> 00:40:23.106
so if I'm gonna die
tonight. I'd like to know.

613
00:40:23.130 --> 00:40:24.266
Okay. you wanna know?

614
00:40:24.290 --> 00:40:28.130
When you were my ta.
you had limitless potential.

615
00:40:28.800 --> 00:40:31.986
You had a mind that I thought
would set the world ablaze.

616
00:40:32.010 --> 00:40:33.276
But you didn't.

617
00:40:33.300 --> 00:40:36.720
You became a drudge.
and a nag. and a bore.

618
00:40:37.220 --> 00:40:38.560
Why did you do it?

619
00:40:40.310 --> 00:40:42.376
Tell me. Howard.
Why did you kill Nancy?

620
00:40:42.400 --> 00:40:45.520
'Cause I wanted to show
her. but she wouldn't listen.

621
00:40:53.780 --> 00:40:54.966
What are we doing down here?

622
00:40:54.990 --> 00:40:55.990
Look.

623
00:40:57.740 --> 00:40:58.886
What am I looking at?

624
00:40:58.910 --> 00:41:00.040
This!

625
00:41:00.870 --> 00:41:02.766
- The bridge?
- The colonnade.

626
00:41:02.790 --> 00:41:06.040
I think there's nothing
more beautiful at night.

627
00:41:07.210 --> 00:41:08.510
I'm cold.

628
00:41:09.300 --> 00:41:11.260
It's something right in your backyard.

629
00:41:11.930 --> 00:41:14.576
And you've probably never
seen it from this angle before.

630
00:41:14.600 --> 00:41:17.286
I'm not in the mood for
your metaphors right now.

631
00:41:17.310 --> 00:41:18.366
Can we go back?

632
00:41:18.390 --> 00:41:20.230
Wait. I have to say something.

633
00:41:22.690 --> 00:41:23.826
I'm in love with you.

634
00:41:23.850 --> 00:41:26.610
- Howard. please...
- wait. wait. wait. Let me finish.

635
00:41:27.270 --> 00:41:29.626
We can be together. I've planned it.

636
00:41:29.650 --> 00:41:31.376
I've stashed money away.

637
00:41:31.400 --> 00:41:33.176
I don't want that.

638
00:41:33.200 --> 00:41:36.886
You were never happier or more alive
than you were in that theater at night.

639
00:41:36.910 --> 00:41:38.176
- What?
- I could feel

640
00:41:38.200 --> 00:41:40.440
- the passion that I awoke in you.
- You are delusional!

641
00:41:44.370 --> 00:41:45.380
Come back here.

642
00:41:47.130 --> 00:41:48.130
No.

643
00:41:49.250 --> 00:41:50.710
This has to stop.

644
00:41:51.920 --> 00:41:53.050
I have to tell her.

645
00:41:54.010 --> 00:41:55.010
You don't mean that.

646
00:41:55.640 --> 00:41:58.866
She may never speak to me again.
but she deserves to know the truth.

647
00:41:58.890 --> 00:42:00.720
Come on. You don't
give a fuck about Mary.

648
00:42:12.740 --> 00:42:14.740
She would be alive if it wasn't for you.

649
00:42:17.990 --> 00:42:19.426
What the hell are you doing?

650
00:42:19.450 --> 00:42:21.330
She wasn't the fragile one.

651
00:42:22.620 --> 00:42:23.660
You were.

652
00:42:27.290 --> 00:42:29.130
You fucking bitch!

653
00:42:35.430 --> 00:42:36.470
Gotcha.

654
00:42:50.730 --> 00:42:51.730
You blew it.

655
00:42:52.480 --> 00:42:53.690
We could have been…

656
00:42:54.700 --> 00:42:56.910
We could have been…
we could have been…

657
00:42:57.490 --> 00:42:58.740
We could have been…

658
00:43:24.020 --> 00:43:25.020
God.

659
00:43:25.600 --> 00:43:28.076
Mare. Mary. Mary!

660
00:43:28.100 --> 00:43:30.876
My god. Wake up.
please. Please wake up.

661
00:43:30.900 --> 00:43:31.980
God. God.

662
00:43:39.820 --> 00:43:41.660
No! No!

663
00:43:59.130 --> 00:44:00.316
It's okay.

664
00:44:00.340 --> 00:44:01.350
We're okay.

665
00:44:01.970 --> 00:44:04.036
You're okay. God.

666
00:44:04.060 --> 00:44:06.520
- God. We…
- we're okay.

667
00:44:07.060 --> 00:44:08.190
We're okay.

668
00:44:20.280 --> 00:44:21.280
Thank you.

669
00:44:22.200 --> 00:44:25.740
- I'm sorry. are you family?
- Yes. I'm going with her. Mary.

670
00:44:26.540 --> 00:44:27.540
Ellie.

671
00:44:33.630 --> 00:44:34.630
You okay?

672
00:44:38.220 --> 00:44:39.550
Are you?

673
00:44:41.470 --> 00:44:42.470
I don't know.

674
00:44:45.970 --> 00:44:47.470
I don't know.

675
00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:13.460
We were supposed to grow old together.

676
00:45:14.130 --> 00:45:18.550
That was the agreement. It was a
promise made when we were young.

677
00:45:19.170 --> 00:45:22.510
Young enough not to know
the terrible irony of friendship.

678
00:45:23.340 --> 00:45:28.180
That the deeper you love someone. the
more agonizing the pain when they're gone.

679
00:45:50.540 --> 00:45:54.016
There's a temptation.
after so much heartbreak.

680
00:45:54.040 --> 00:45:55.750
to become an island.

681
00:45:56.460 --> 00:45:58.090
But that's a mistake.

682
00:45:59.300 --> 00:46:02.670
Staying available to love is worth the risk.

683
00:46:03.470 --> 00:46:09.470
To keep reaching for that
deeper sense of joy and belonging.

684
00:46:36.750 --> 00:46:40.340
I'd like to say all that pain
we went through was a gift.

685
00:46:40.920 --> 00:46:42.606
That it taught us how strong we are.

686
00:46:42.630 --> 00:46:43.880
How capable of healing.

687
00:46:45.130 --> 00:46:49.576
But after everything we've been through.
we could never lose the bond we share.

688
00:46:49.600 --> 00:46:51.520
Our friendship is too powerful.

689
00:46:52.470 --> 00:46:55.390
It should be able to
survive just about anything.

690
00:46:57.100 --> 00:46:59.980
At least for now.

690
00:47:00.305 --> 00:48:00.152
